div.p:
—develop and maintain a “special relationship” with the US, which it sees as the ultimate protector of the Saudi kingdom
                    from external subversion, and as a major source of the technology needed for the
                    kingdom’s development;

—lack of trained manpower, which makes it difficult to staff ministries at home
                    and diplomatic posts abroad with qualified personnel, and tends to concentrate
                    all decision-making responsibilities on the top leadership;
